cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.AR, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper presents an NS-2 module to simulate different access methods on a shared link, which is a networking topic. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the impact of different access methods on transport layer performance, which can be related to information theory. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a possibility as the paper mentions the implementation details of the module, which can be related to hardware architecture. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possibility as the paper mentions satellite communication, which can involve multimedia data transmission. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on security or cryptography, but it is still a possibility as the module can be used to evaluate the security of different access methods.
